quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  82,1,"When the heaven is split asunder,",footnotes:182617:1
  82,2,"when the stars are scattered,"
  82,3,"when the seas are made to burst forth,"
  82,4,"and when graves are laid open,",footnotes:182618:1
  82,5,"everyone shall know all his deeds, both the earlier and the later.",footnotes:182619:1
  82,6,"O man! What has deceived you about your generous Lord"
  82,7,"Who created you, shaped you, and made you well-proportioned,"
  82,8,"and set you in whatever form He pleased?",footnotes:182620:1
  82,9,"No indeed; (the fact is that) you deny the Reckoning, declaring it a lie;",footnotes:182621:1,footnotes:182622:2
  82,10,"you do so the while there are watchers over you;"
  83,1,"Woe to the stinters;",footnotes:182625:1
  83,2,"those who, when they take from others by measure, take their full share;",footnotes:182626:1
  83,3,"but who, when they measure or weigh for others, give less than their due."
  83,4,"Do they not realise that they will be raised to life"
  83,5,"on a Great Day,",footnotes:182627:1
  83,6,"a Day when mankind will stand before the Lord of the Universe?"